ENTRY       EC 3.2.1.38                 Enzyme
NAME        beta-D-fucosidase;
            beta-fucosidase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Glycosylases;
            Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
SYSNAME     beta-D-fucoside fucohydrolase
REACTION    Hydrolysis of terminal non-reducing beta-D-fucose residues in beta-D-fucosides
COMMENT     Enzymes from some sources also hydrolyse beta-D-galactosides and/or beta-D-glucosides and/or alpha-L-arabinosides. The activity of EC 3.2.1.37 xylan 1,4-beta-xylosidase, is an associated activity found in some sources (e.g. liver).
HISTORY     EC 3.2.1.38 created 1965, deleted 1972, reinstated 1978
